Class FromParseableArgumentType<T extends Parseable<TInner>,TInner>

java.lang.Object
lanat.utils.errors.ErrorContainerImpl<ArgumentTypeError>
lanat.ArgumentType<TInner>
lanat.argumentTypes.FromParseableArgumentType<T,TInner>
Type Parameters:
T - The Parseable type.
TInner - The type of the value returned by the Parseable.parseValues(String[]) method.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Parseable<TInner>, ErrorContainer<ArgumentTypeError>, NamedWithDescription, ParentElementGetter<ArgumentType<?>>, PostCreationInheritor<Command>, Resettable
public class FromParseableArgumentType<T extends Parseable<TInner>,TInner> extends ArgumentType<TInner>
An argument type that uses a Parseable to parse values. If the Parseable.parseValues(String[]) method returns null, an error is added. The error message can be specified in the constructor.
